===subject:Cortes
===from:Amy Metzger
===email:ptflute@bellsouth.net
===date:Thu Sep 11 15:38:55 2003
===message:I think it is very naive to think he would have listened.  First of all, remember the difference in the cultures.  Cortes was looking for gold and riches and considered the natives he found to be less than worthy of consideration.  In other words, they were inferior to his own people.  Although the natives were "civilized", he didn't recognize with the clarity that we have looking back that their culture was worthy of leaving intact.  He was determined to fulfill his duty to his original goals.  
