===message:I have to agree with Amy, the cultures were very different. As she said most likely the Spanish considered the Native Americas as sub-human, therefore anything that was done to them was AOK. Also I think the men who went and did all those things to the women were of a different mindset, some people just don't think about the consequences of what they do or how they might affect other people and quite frankly women weren't viewed in too good of a light at that time anyway <in Europe>, but that doesn't excuse what they did. If I had a chance to talk to Cortez I honestly wouldn't even waste my time talking to a person such as him. I mean if he can do the things he did would the words of a rational person have any kind of effect on him instead of the pleading of his victims? And dang I could never understand why those who conquer have such a desire to destroy anything and everything that wasn't built by their hands or written using their words. I think that's a trait of all who go out to conquer. It seems only the people who clean up the mess have the time or the inclination to think about everything that has been lost as a consequence. 
